The Hart Mason Index is a method for the identification and classification of project issues. The index provides a way to grade projects that have issues and provides a situational awareness to stakeholders and possible consequences, including litigation and criminal prosecution.
Assessment and grading according to the Hart Mason Index is carried out during the execution of a project, that normally span the following stages:
Euphoria and Excitement
Disenchantment
Search for the Guilty
Punishment of the Innocent
Reward for the Uninvolved
The ten point scale is intended to inform management of the severity of the issues and the likely consequences.
Disappointment
Mishap
Malfunction
Failure
Crisis
Calamity
Debacle
Fiasco
Disaster
Catastrophe
